# isync/mbsync config — COHS Microsoft 365 via XOAUTH2.
#
# This file is symlinked to ~/.mbsyncrc via dotter.
#
# Prerequisites (macOS):
#   - mbsync (isync) built from upstream against Homebrew cyrus-sasl
#     with the cyrus-sasl-xoauth2 plugin installed. Installed at
#     ~/.local/bin/mbsync (takes PATH precedence over /opt/homebrew/bin).
#   - practiceforge binary in ~/.local/bin/, stable-codesigned with
#     identifier `com.williamnapier.practiceforge` so the keychain ACL
#     survives rebuilds. `email imap-token` prints a fresh Outlook IMAP
#     OAuth bearer on stdout; refresh-on-read is handled internally, so
#     no separate refresh timer is strictly required (though a periodic
#     `m365-imap-refresh` can run as a keep-warm).
#
# First-time setup (once per install, interactive device-code flow):
#   practiceforge email imap-init --account cohs
#
# On Linux (nimbini): distribution package cyrus-sasl-xoauth2 drops the
# plugin into the system SASL dir; stock mbsync from the distro works
# out of the box. Same mbsyncrc contents. Same `imap-init` step.

IMAPAccount cohs
Host outlook.office365.com
Port 993
User will.napier@changeofharleystreet.com
AuthMechs XOAUTH2
# PassCmd output is used as the SASL XOAUTH2 token. practiceforge's
# refresh-on-read logic (KeychainOAuthTokenSource) silently mints a new
# access token if the cached one is within 5 min of expiry, so the
# printed token is always fresh at the moment of use.
PassCmd "$HOME/.local/bin/practiceforge email imap-token --account cohs"
SSLType IMAPS
# macOS trust store is used implicitly; no CertificateFile needed.

IMAPStore cohs-remote
Account cohs

MaildirStore cohs-local
Path ~/Mail/cohs/
Inbox ~/Mail/cohs/INBOX/
SubFolders Verbatim

# Sync all standard M365/Exchange folders. Pull-only: COHS IMAP is
# authoritative, local is a read-only mirror. If mutation from local-side
# Meli is wanted later, change `Sync Pull` to `Sync All`.
#
# Patterns list matches typical Exchange Online folder names. The `!`
# prefix excludes: we drop the "Conversation History", "RSS Subscriptions",
# "Outbox" and a few other Outlook-internal folders that typically contain
# nothing useful. Add more patterns (or `*` to catch everything) if
# additional folders appear over time.

Channel cohs-all
Far :cohs-remote:
Near :cohs-local:
Patterns "INBOX" "Sent Items" "Drafts" "Archive" "Deleted Items" "Junk Email"
Sync Pull
Expunge None
CopyArrivalDate yes
Create Near
SyncState *

# Historical single-INBOX channel, kept for explicit "just pull inbox" invocations.
Channel cohs-inbox
Far :cohs-remote:INBOX
Near :cohs-local:INBOX
Sync Pull
Expunge None
CopyArrivalDate yes
Create Near
SyncState *

# Convenience group so `mbsync cohs` syncs everything COHS-related.
Group cohs
Channel cohs-all

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gmail (personal) via IMAP + XOAUTH2.
#
# This is the Phase-2 migration path: mbsync pulls Gmail via IMAP into
# ~/Mail/gmail-imap/ in PARALLEL with the legacy lieer/gmi path that
# pulls to ~/Mail/personal/. Keeping them separate during cutover means
# a bad mbsync run cannot destroy lieer-indexed state. Once the new
# path is verified (mail arrives, tags round-trip via the
# practiceforge-email-gmail-push-tags tool), notmuch's index path is
# swapped and lieer is retired.
#
# XOAUTH2 token is produced by `practiceforge email imap-token
# --account gmail`, which delegates to gmail_oauth::show() (refresh-on-
# read against Google's /token endpoint). The same OAuth tokens
# himalaya uses — no separate consent required. Scope is the Gmail
# full-access `https://mail.google.com/` which covers IMAP, SMTP, AND
# modify-labels (needed for push-tags), so nothing further to consent.
#
# Gmail's IMAP emulates labels as folders. A message with N labels
# appears in N folders. notmuch dedupes by Message-ID, so search stays
# correct, but disk footprint scales with avg labels per message. To
# keep that sane, we sync `[Gmail]/All Mail` + a curated subset of
# useful label-folders, not every label.

IMAPAccount gmail
Host imap.gmail.com
Port 993
User will@willnapier.com
AuthMechs XOAUTH2
PassCmd "$HOME/.local/bin/practiceforge email imap-token --account gmail"
SSLType IMAPS

IMAPStore gmail-remote
Account gmail

MaildirStore gmail-local
Path ~/Mail/gmail-imap/
Inbox ~/Mail/gmail-imap/INBOX/
SubFolders Verbatim

# Pattern `*` matches lieer's full-mirror behaviour: pull everything
# Gmail exposes over IMAP. A message with N labels shows up in N
# folders (Gmail's IMAP label-as-folder emulation). notmuch dedupes
# by Message-ID so search is unaffected, but disk use scales with
# average labels per message. Expect ~2–3× the All-Mail size for a
# heavily-labelled account. Narrow if disk becomes an issue:
#   Patterns "[Gmail]/All Mail" "INBOX" "[Gmail]/Sent Mail" \
#            "[Gmail]/Drafts" "[Gmail]/Trash" "[Gmail]/Spam"
# (the bracketed namespace needs mbsync to see Gmail's hierarchy
# delimiter; PathDelimiter "/" on IMAPAccount sets this explicitly if
# the default probe doesn't pick it up).
Channel gmail-all
Far :gmail-remote:
Near :gmail-local:
Patterns *
Sync Pull
Expunge None
CopyArrivalDate yes
Create Near
SyncState *

Group gmail
Channel gmail-all
